==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Gurnet
<hw>Gur"net</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>
}</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF. <ets>gornal</ets>, <ets>gournal</ets>,
<ets>gornart</ets>, perh. akin to F. <ets>grogner</ets> to
<ets>grunt</ets>; cf. Ir. <ets>guirnead</ets> gurnard.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>One ofseveral European marine fishes, of the
genus <gen>Trigla</gen> and allied genera, having a large and spiny
head, with mailed cheeks. Some of the species are highly esteemed for
food. The name is sometimes applied to the American sea robins.</def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>gournet</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Plyling gurnard</b></col>. <cd>See under
<er>Flying</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gurniad</ent>⟦br⟧
